var __index = {"config":{"lang":["en"],"separator":"[\\s\\-\\.]","pipeline":["stopWordFilter"]},"docs":[{"location":"index.html","title":"Home","text":""},{"location":"index.html#breaking-down-barriers-to-sharing-knowledge","title":"Breaking Down Barriers to Sharing Knowledge","text":"<p>Exploring the Intersection of Machine Learning and Chemistry</p> <p>Welcome to Zhuyf's Wiki</p> <p>Contact Me Wiki Directory</p>"},{"location":"index.html#about-me","title":"About Me","text":"<p>I'm ZhuYifei, a computational chemistry PhD student specializing in machine learning and non-adiabatic dynamics.</p> <p>\"Knowledge should have no barriers.\"</p>"},{"location":"index.html#interests-expertise","title":"Interests &amp; Expertise","text":""},{"location":"index.html#machine-learning-ai","title":"Machine Learning &amp; AI","text":"<ul> <li>Deep learning applications</li> <li>AI model development</li> <li>Interdisciplinary AI solutions</li> </ul>"},{"location":"index.html#computational-chemistry","title":"Computational Chemistry","text":"<ul> <li>Non-adiabatic dynamics</li> <li>Quantum chemical calculations</li> <li>Molecular simulations</li> </ul>"},{"location":"index.html#web-development","title":"Web Development","text":"<ul> <li>Full-stack development</li> <li>Scientific web applications</li> <li>Interactive visualization</li> </ul>"},{"location":"index.html#get-in-touch","title":"Get in Touch","text":"<p>I'm always open to collaboration and academic discussions. Feel free to reach out through any of the channels below.</p> <p> Email  GitHub  Gitee</p>"},{"location":"wiki/index.html","title":"Wiki Directory","text":""},{"location":"wiki/index.html#computational-chemistry","title":"Computational Chemistry","text":""},{"location":"wiki/index.html#quantum-chemistry","title":"Quantum Chemistry","text":"<ul> <li>Gibbs Free Energy in ORR</li> </ul>"},{"location":"wiki/index.html#machine-learning","title":"Machine Learning","text":"<ul> <li>Coming soon...</li> </ul>"},{"location":"wiki/index.html#non-adiabatic-dynamics","title":"Non-adiabatic Dynamics","text":"<ul> <li>Coming soon...</li> </ul>"},{"location":"wiki/index.html#programming-notes","title":"Programming Notes","text":""},{"location":"wiki/index.html#web-development","title":"Web Development","text":"<ul> <li>Coming soon...</li> </ul>"},{"location":"wiki/index.html#scientific-computing","title":"Scientific Computing","text":"<ul> <li>Coming soon...</li> </ul>"},{"location":"wiki/index.html#ai-applications","title":"AI Applications","text":"<ul> <li>Coming soon...</li> </ul>"},{"location":"wiki/tags.html","title":"Tags","text":""},{"location":"wiki/tags.html#tag:ai","title":"AI","text":"<ul> <li>            Learning Source          </li> </ul>"},{"location":"wiki/tags.html#tag:gaussian","title":"Gaussian","text":"<ul> <li>            Gibbs Free Energy Calculation for O\u2082 to H\u2082O\u2082 Reaction          </li> </ul>"},{"location":"wiki/tags.html#tag:linux","title":"Linux","text":"<ul> <li>            Learning Source          </li> </ul>"},{"location":"wiki/tags.html#tag:ml","title":"ML","text":"<ul> <li>            Learning Source          </li> </ul>"},{"location":"wiki/tags.html#tag:physical-chemistry","title":"Physical Chemistry","text":"<ul> <li>            Gibbs Free Energy Calculation for O\u2082 to H\u2082O\u2082 Reaction          </li> </ul>"},{"location":"wiki/tags.html#tag:qm-calculation","title":"QM Calculation","text":"<ul> <li>            Gibbs Free Energy Calculation for O\u2082 to H\u2082O\u2082 Reaction          </li> </ul>"},{"location":"wiki/ml/studying.html","title":"Recommended Learning Resources","text":"","tags":["ML","AI","Linux"]},{"location":"wiki/ml/studying.html#machine-learning","title":"Machine Learning","text":"","tags":["ML","AI","Linux"]},{"location":"wiki/ml/studying.html#ml-programing","title":"ML Programing","text":"Link Note https://zh-v2.d2l.ai/ Dive in to Deep Learning by Mu Li et al. https://nn.labml.ai/ Annotated Research Paper Implementations https://github.com/lucidrains Phillip Wang's Github repository (About P. Wang) https://bohrium.dp.tech/ DPTechnology","tags":["ML","AI","Linux"]},{"location":"wiki/ml/studying.html#algorithm","title":"Algorithm","text":"Link Note https://github.com/mli/paper-reading paper-reading by Mu Li https://lilianweng.github.io/ Blog of Lilian Weng https://spaces.ac.cn/category/Big-Data Blog of Jianlin Su https://yang-song.net/blog/ Blog of Yang Song https://distill.pub/ Showing code with animation https://ppwwyyxx.com/blog/ Blog of Yuxin Wu (Author of Detectron2) https://machinelearningmastery.com/blog/ Jason Brownlee's Blog","tags":["ML","AI","Linux"]},{"location":"wiki/ml/studying.html#community","title":"Community","text":"Link Note https://towardsdatascience.com/ Towards Data Science https://www.kaggle.com/code Kaggle https://github.com/josephmisiti/awesome-machine-learning awesome-machine-learning repository covers almost every aspect of machine learning resources.","tags":["ML","AI","Linux"]},{"location":"wiki/qm_cal/gibbs_ORR.html","title":"Gibbs Free Energy Calculation for O\u2082 to H\u2082O\u2082 Reaction","text":"<p>This wiki provides a concise guide on calculating the Gibbs free energy (\u0394G) for the reaction where O\u2082 is reduced to H\u2082O\u2082 via a 2-electron oxygen reduction reaction (ORR) pathway on a catalyst surface (*). The process is key to understanding catalyst efficiency in producing H\u2082O\u2082.</p>","tags":["QM Calculation","Gaussian","Physical Chemistry"]},{"location":"wiki/qm_cal/gibbs_ORR.html#reaction-pathway","title":"Reaction Pathway","text":"<p>The ORR pathway involves these steps:</p> <ol> <li>O\u2082(g) \u2192 *O\u2082: O\u2082 adsorbs onto the catalyst.</li> <li>*O\u2082 + H\u207a + e\u207b \u2192 *OOH: Proton-electron transfer forms *OOH.</li> <li>*OOH + H\u207a + e\u207b \u2192 *HOOH: Another transfer forms *HOOH (adsorbed H\u2082O\u2082).</li> <li>*HOOH \u2192 H\u2082O\u2082(l) + *: H\u2082O\u2082 desorbs into liquid phase.</li> </ol>","tags":["QM Calculation","Gaussian","Physical Chemistry"]},{"location":"wiki/qm_cal/gibbs_ORR.html#calculating-g","title":"Calculating \u0394G","text":"","tags":["QM Calculation","Gaussian","Physical Chemistry"]},{"location":"wiki/qm_cal/gibbs_ORR.html#general-formula","title":"General Formula","text":"<p>For each step:</p> \\[ \\Delta G = \\Delta E + \\Delta \\text{ZPE} - T \\times \\Delta S \\] <ul> <li>\u0394E: Electronic energy change (from DFT).</li> <li>\u0394ZPE: Zero-point energy change.</li> <li>T \u00d7 \u0394S: Entropy contribution (T = 298.15 K).</li> </ul> <p>Proton-electron steps use the computational hydrogen electrode (CHE) model: \\(G(\\text{H}^+ + \\text{e}^-) = \\frac{1}{2} G(\\text{H}_2)\\) at U = 0 V, pH = 0.</p>","tags":["QM Calculation","Gaussian","Physical Chemistry"]},{"location":"wiki/qm_cal/gibbs_ORR.html#step-by-step-g","title":"Step-by-Step \u0394G","text":"<ol> <li>O\u2082(g) \u2192 *O\u2082:    \\(\\Delta G_1 = G(*\\text{O}_2) - G(*) - G(\\text{O}_2\\text{(g)})\\)</li> <li>*O\u2082 + H\u207a + e\u207b \u2192 *OOH:    \\(\\Delta G_2 = G(*\\text{OOH}) - G(*\\text{O}_2) - \\frac{1}{2} G(\\text{H}_2)\\)</li> <li>*OOH + H\u207a + e\u207b \u2192 *HOOH:    \\(\\Delta G_3 = G(*\\text{HOOH}) - G(*\\text{OOH}) - \\frac{1}{2} G(\\text{H}_2)\\)</li> <li>*HOOH \u2192 H\u2082O\u2082(l) + *:    \\(\\Delta G_4 = G(*) + G(\\text{H}_2\\text{O}_2\\text{(l)}) - G(*\\text{HOOH})\\)</li> </ol>","tags":["QM Calculation","Gaussian","Physical Chemistry"]},{"location":"wiki/qm_cal/gibbs_ORR.html#other-considerations","title":"Other Considerations","text":"","tags":["QM Calculation","Gaussian","Physical Chemistry"]},{"location":"wiki/qm_cal/gibbs_ORR.html#delta-g_u-electrode-potential","title":"\\(\\Delta G_U\\): Electrode Potential","text":"<p>\\(\\Delta G_U = -n \\times e \\times U\\)</p> <ul> <li>\\(n\\): Number of electrons (1 per proton-electron step).</li> <li>\\(U\\): Electrode potential (V vs. SHE).</li> </ul> <p>Set \\(U = 0\\) V for baseline; adjust as needed.</p>","tags":["QM Calculation","Gaussian","Physical Chemistry"]},{"location":"wiki/qm_cal/gibbs_ORR.html#delta-g_textph-ph-effect","title":"\\(\\Delta G_{\\text{pH}}\\): pH Effect","text":"<p>\\(\\Delta G_{\\text{pH}} = 0.0592 \\times \\text{pH} \\, \\text{(eV)}\\)</p> <ul> <li>pH = 0 (acidic): \\(\\Delta G_{\\text{pH}} = 0\\).</li> <li>Adjust for other pH values (e.g., pH = 7 \u2192 0.414 eV).</li> </ul>","tags":["QM Calculation","Gaussian","Physical Chemistry"]},{"location":"wiki/qm_cal/gibbs_ORR.html#entropy-s-calculation","title":"Entropy (\\(S\\)) Calculation","text":"<p>If you calculate \\(\u0394G\\) using Gaussian, the \\(G\\) can be obtained directly. Otherwise, you might need to calculate \\(\u0394G\\) with \\(\u0394S\\).</p> <ul> <li>Adsorbed Species: From frequency analysis (e.g., VASP):</li> <li>Vibrational factor: \\(x_i = \\frac{100 \\times c \\times h \\times \\nu_i}{k_B \\times T}\\).</li> <li>Partition function: \\(p f_i = \\frac{x_i}{e^{x_i} - 1} - \\log(1 - e^{-x_i})\\).</li> <li>Total entropy: \\(S = \\frac{R \\times \\sum p f_i}{1000 \\times 96.485}\\) (eV/K).</li> <li>Gas Phase (O\u2082, H\u2082, H\u2082O\u2082): Use Gaussian 16 (6-311G* basis) to calculate vibrational, rotational, and translational contributions.</li> </ul>","tags":["QM Calculation","Gaussian","Physical Chemistry"]},{"location":"wiki/qm_cal/gibbs_ORR.html#free-energy-diagram","title":"Free Energy Diagram","text":"<ul> <li>Reference: O\u2082(g) + * = 0 eV.</li> <li>Plot: *O\u2082 (\u0394G\u2081), *OOH (\u0394G\u2081 + \u0394G\u2082), *HOOH (\u0394G\u2081 + \u0394G\u2082 + \u0394G\u2083), H\u2082O\u2082(l) + * (\u0394G\u2081 + \u0394G\u2082 + \u0394G\u2083 + \u0394G\u2084).</li> </ul>","tags":["QM Calculation","Gaussian","Physical Chemistry"]},{"location":"wiki/qm_cal/gibbs_ORR.html#key-points-to-note","title":"Key Points to Note","text":"<ul> <li>O\u2082(g) Correction: DFT underestimates O\u2082(g) stability. Use:$$   G(\\text{O}_2\\text{(g)}) = 2G(\\text{H}_2\\text{O}) - 2G(\\text{H}_2) + 4.92 \\, \\text{eV}   $$</li> <li>H\u2082O\u2082(l) Adjustment: Convert $G(\\text{H}_2\\text{O}_2\\text{(g)}) $ to liquid phase:   \\(G(\\text{H}_2\\text{O}_2\\text{(l)}) = G(\\text{H}_2\\text{O}_2\\text{(g)}) - 0.28 \\, \\text{eV}\\)</li> <li>Adsorption Sites: Optimize *O\u2082, *OOH, *HOOH configurations for stability.</li> <li>Consistency: Use identical DFT settings for all species.</li> <li>Corrections: Include ZPE, entropy, $ \\Delta G_U $, and $ \\Delta G_{\\text{pH}} $ if needed.</li> </ul>","tags":["QM Calculation","Gaussian","Physical Chemistry"]},{"location":"wiki/qm_cal/gibbs_ORR.html#summary","title":"Summary","text":"<p>Accurate \u0394G calculation for O\u2082 to H\u2082O\u2082 requires precise energy terms, gas-phase corrections, and consistent methods. These steps enable a reliable free energy diagram for evaluating ORR catalysts.</p>","tags":["QM Calculation","Gaussian","Physical Chemistry"]}]}